			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">What I mean is that the pet spell are spells.    A wholesale upgrat affects all the pets all the time.  Even element specific ones do to a certain extent.    Augments allow an amount of modification to a single pet cast.
<br />

<br />
Mele have a variety of different approaches available to them.  Flexability etc.  While there are only a limited number of spells that can upgrade a mage, or any other caster for that matter, Equipment has a much more immediate effect on upgrades for mele, than for casters  Mele are more their equipment than caster are.  
<br />

<br />
What the augment idea does is to suplement the balancing that is taking place now.  It would take the base and focused pet, and allow us to tweak it so that it will fit a situation better than the base.  In a sense it becomes the pets Equipment.
<br />

<br />
I'm not saying we don't need more focii, or we don't need other balancing.  What I'm saying is a pet in  solo / exp group / and raid have different roles / uses.  By being able to augment the pet, we can tailor the pet to the role it needs to fill, without overpowering the pet in other situations.  
<br />

<br />
Typical raid, pet should not be taking direct mele damage.  So augment the pet so that it hits harder  / maxes more often, or has bane damage for that type of MoB, and withstands AE's  better.  To have ALL of the augment one may have to spend time aquireing them.  But it will make the pet perform better for raids.
<br />

<br />
For a group where the Pet may have to off tank quite a bit more then his ability to do damage isn't as important as being a getto form of crowd control,  keeping 2nd MoB busy while the group deals with the first.  More than a speed bump.  Then we would want to augment the pet to have better damage avoidance, and higher hp Ac etc..  
<br />

<br />
Solo where the pet needs to do both take damage and avoid it, it would have to be a blend.
<br />

<br />
Just as there is no one mele dicipline that handles all situations, thats why there is more than one, A single focus / augment  should not / cannot work in all situations.
<br />

<br />
When there are Heavy casting MoB augment the pet to proc as stun as well as the Air pets Natural casting.  Wehn there are MoB that buff themselves heavily, Augment the pet to have cancel magic or other buff stripping procs.
<br />

<br />
And also, and most important in my opinion it will allow mages to become more unique..  Allowing is to augment the pet to our playstyle.   We can improve a pet in a particular area as we deem.
<br />

<br />
You perfer a pet that does this, I prefer a pet that does that.  Right now either one of us gets what we like, or neither of us do.  With augments We can both have it.  without the unbalancing facter of the pet having both this and that all the time.<br />_________________<br />Elawise Fyremountain</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
