And thanks for not flaming.  
<br />

<br />
Most of us here are smart.  I believe we can come up with creative idea's that will help us all in any situation.  
<br />

<br />
At first I though that augmenting the pets equipment would be the best route.  But the idea of carrying around 2 full sets of equipment and the blowing of a full mana bar just to get started was probably not the most elegant solution.
<br />

<br />
Who knows component augments  may open up a whole new area for individuality for all casters.  But I would prefer to see how is can be handled with pets first.  Then if it is as open and useful as I think it can be, other spells that require components can be added to the "Augmentable" spell lists.
<br />

<br />
I know situational has become a four letter word around here.  But it doesn't have to be.  If we can convince Sony that different area's can be addressed on a more case by case, or encounter by encounter basis by giving player more options, we would all be the better for it.<br />_________________<br />Elawise Fyremountain</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
